reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I didn't know what to expect when I received such a small box. The fan is pleasantly surprising and great quality. I love that it clips to my headboard and is fully swivel for my individual needs. The only down fall is the safety cover can easily be fall off which I rectified with a twist tie. It's easy to clean and maintain. It's compact for travel but really puts out the airflow as needed. I will look to this company for all my future fan purchases.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet and Does it’s Job
reviews.reviewText: What a perfect little fan for a desk or a bedside table. Super adjustable - you can angle this thing however you want. And it gives off a surprising breeze for its tiny size. And it’s super quiet. On its lowest two settings you can barely hear it. On the highest setting it gets a little noisy but the middle setting is all you need. Again, it’s best for clamping on a shelf at your desk or on your bedside table or headboard - don’t expect this thing to cool off your entire office or workshop. But it does it’s job as a tiny personal fan. And it does it well. Great product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great fan - BAD plug!
reviews.reviewText: Great, quiet, small fan, but the plug broke off with little use. I had to replace it with another type. I did like the way it sat flat bottomed by itself if not clipped onto something.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small but mighty
reviews.reviewText: This fan is awesome. I just bought my second one for another room. It's amazing how powerful it is. When you see it, you would think the power would be so-so. That is not the case. I have never had to use the third setting! I highly recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet and powerful
reviews.reviewText: I was very shocked to see how small this fan was once it arrived and was nervous it wasn't going to work all that well as a result. I was very surprised when I used it though, as it was powerful and quiet. It clipped onto the bed frame nicely, and did a great job keeping me cool through the night. I used this while traveling, as I have to have a fan blowing on me to sleep. In the end, I was happy with the small size as it fits nicely in my luggage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great but loud and squeaky
reviews.reviewText: This fan is almost great, it’s has three different temperatures. It would be the perfect fan if it didn’t make so much noise, it vibrates against the headboard and it makes a screeching sound. Overall, it’s a decent deal for the price but I have only had it for a month and it’s too late to return and I don’t know if I can deal with how loud it is.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works great for my treadmill.
reviews.reviewText: It seems like this has a pretty good range of uses, from being a little fan for your office to clipping to a treadmill to cool you down during a run. I do the latter and it works great, it plugs right into my treadmill and can be attached to the top of the screen with the clip.It has three fan speed settings and produces a pretty good airflow for such a small fan.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Would buy again
reviews.reviewText: It is a pretty good little fan. It is not too loud and pretty powerful. I use it when I sleep.

I got this fan to use at work. All of us at work fight over the temperature all the time. I’m always sweating, so my manager felt bad that I was always melting and found this on Amazon and sent me the link. I thought we’ll why not I’ll give it a go. Brought it into work on wendsday, it plugs into the computer with its USB port, clipped it onto the counter and faced it towards my station. I’m right next to the desk. Turned it on and it’s pretty powerful. I love how I can just turn it in the direction I need it in. It’s fantastic. I haven’t had to tie my hair back all week. That’s a big deal. It kept me comfortable all week. The girls are happy I’m not turning on the air conditioner and I’m comfortable with my little fan. I’m so pleased. The claw is strong to. I’m surprised it is able to hook onto larger things. Anyway love love love it.

Despite its small size, the airflow is large and quiet,The angle is well adjusted.The only disappointing thing is that the fan cover comes off if you hit it a little.Rotates smoothly and quietly with no vibrationThe strength of the clip is very reliable.

reviews.reviewTitle: Works wonders, but makes ticking sound
reviews.reviewText: Small yet powerful, exactly what I was looking for. Update: Started making ticking sound, maybe fan is not fully secure. Update: customer service responsive and very good, adding a star.
This fan is clipped to my headboard and cools me of nicely throughout the night. It's nice and quiet too so it's not waking up my momster(wife) at night! Thanks!
The three speed option is very nice. It moves the air very well for such a small fan. It will really help on those super hot summer days in my Skoolie! Cheers.
